    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920612>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Paracophus velazquezi n. sp. A. Male habitus in lateral view. B. and dorsal view. C. frons. D. female head, and thorax in dorsal view. E. female abdomen in dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4920612/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920618>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Paracophus victoriensis n. sp. A. Male habitus in lateral view. B. and dorsal view. C. frons. D. abdomen in dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4920618/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920610>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Tohila atelomma female allotype. Habitus in lateral view, mid and hind legs. Photo: Holger Braun." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4920610/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920632>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Hubbellcophus placonotus n. comb. Paratype. A. Male habitus in lateral and B. dorsal view. Photos: Holger Braun." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4920632/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920638>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Hubbellcophus species, diagnostic structures. A-D. Head and thorax in lateral view. E-H. habitus in dorsal view. I-J. male tergites modification. A, G. H. caecus n. comb. B, F. H. lippus n. comb. C, E, I. H. cladonotus n. comb. D, H, J. H. placonotus n. comb. (All draws after Hubbell, 1972)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4920638/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920646>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Hubbellcophus caecus n. comb. females in live condition. A. Adult in lateral view. B. Subadult in dorsal view. Both females from Tamaulipas, Gomez Farías. Cueva “La Capilla”. Photos: Diego Barrales-Alcalá. I Naturalist observation: https://www.naturalista.mx/taxa/256710-Paracophus-caecus" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4920646/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920654>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Otteius and Cubacophus male genitalia. A-C. O. thoracicus. D-F. C. gibaraensis. A, D. genitalia apex in ventral view. B, E. genitalia apex in ventral view. C. F. genitalia apex in lateral view. (All draws after Ruíz-Baliú & Otte, 1997)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4920654/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920648>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Venegascophus reddelli n. comb.A. Head and pronotum in lateral view. B. frons. C. head and pronotum in dorsal view. D, E, F. male genitalia in dorsal, ventral and lateral view respectively." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4920648/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920652>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Venegascophus n. gen. and Hortacophus n. gen. A, C, D, E. V. sanctorum n. comb. B, F, G, H. H. apterus n. comb. A, B. head and pronotum in dorsal view. C, F. genitalia apex in dorsal view. D, G. genitalia apex in ventral view. E, H. genitalia apex in lateral view. (All draws after Hubbell, 1972)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4920652/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

